A 'Ribes indecorum' is a flowering shrub that belongs to the Grossulariaceae family.
It is a deciduous shrub that grows up to 1.5 meters tall and 1.5 meters wide.
The leaves of 'Ribes indecorum' are lobed, toothed, and a bright green color.
The flowers are pale pink or white with five petals and hang in pendulous clusters.
The fruit of 'Ribes indecorum' is a small, round, green berry that turns red when ripe.
It is native to western North America and can be found in open woodlands and rocky slopes.
The visual characteristics of 'Ribes indecorum' include delicate pale pink flowers, bright green leaves, and small clusters of red berries.
